{
  "slug": "cloudflare-ztna-application",
  "kind": "terraform",
  "metadata": {
    "name": "Cloudflare Zero Trust Access Application",
    "description": "Creates a Cloudflare Zero Trust Access application with service token and IP-based access policies.",
    "guide": "## Overview\nCreates a Cloudflare Zero Trust Access application with optional service token and IP-based access policies.\n\n## Prerequisites\n- Have the target Cloudflare account and zone IDs ready before rendering the Terraform files.\n- If you enable the service token policy, create the Cloudflare service token first and capture its ID.\n- If you enable the IP policy, review the allowed CIDR ranges carefully and decide whether any lifecycle or dependency rules are required in your workspace.\n\n## Apply\n- Render the Terraform files, then run `terraform fmt`, `terraform plan`, and `terraform apply` in the target workspace.\n- Review the generated access policies before apply so the final rule set matches the intended access model.\n\n## Follow-Up\n- Test both allowed and denied access paths from real client networks after the application is created.\n- Rotate service tokens through your normal change workflow and keep the Terraform state aligned with any policy updates.\n- Confirm the protected hostname is routed where you expect before putting users behind the application.\n\n## References\n- [Cloudflare Zero Trust](https://www.cloudflare.com/zero-trust/)\n- [Terraform Provider](https://registry.terraform.io/providers/cloudflare/cloudflare/latest/docs/resources/zero_trust_access_application)",
    "tags": [],
    "template_version": "5.12.0",
    "icon": {
      "provider": "selfhst",
      "id": "cloudflare-zero-trust"
    },
    "draft": false
  },
  "variables": [
    {
      "title": "Application",
      "name": "application",
      "items": [
        {
          "name": "app_name",
          "type": "str",
          "title": "Application name",
          "required": false,
          "default": "application",
          "description": "Name to use for the application.",
          "config": {
            "placeholder": "application"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "domain",
          "type": "str",
          "title": "Application domain",
          "required": false,
          "description": "Domain used for Application.",
          "config": {
            "placeholder": "app.home.arpa"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "session_duration",
          "type": "str",
          "title": "Session Duration",
          "required": false,
          "default": "15m",
          "description": "Session duration (e.g., 15m, 1h, 24h)",
          "config": {
            "placeholder": "15m"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "General",
